      <description>&lt;p&gt;A bypass capacitor (aka &amp;ldquo;filter cap&amp;rdquo;) is a small capacitor that dampens electrical noise moving toward an IC. Electrical noise can cause circuit malfunctions. Unless otherwise specified in the data sheet of an IC, a 0.1 ÂµF non-polarized ceramic capacitor usually makes a good bypass capacitor.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
